      <hedline>
        <hl1>THE MARKETS: CURRENCIES</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Euro holds near a record low on speculation the European Central Bank will raise interest rates as much as a half-point; graph (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>THE EURO SLIPS. The euro held near a record low on speculation the European Central Bank would raise interest rates as much as a half-point today. In New York, the euro settled at 89.24 cents, down from 89.25 cents.</p>
      </block>
